This week, Dr. Elizabeth Sherwood-Randall, the Assistant to the President for Homeland Security, will lead a U.S. delegation to Uzbekistan for a high-level international conference. The conference aims to promote prosperity, security, and regional connectivity between Central and South Asia. Dr. Sherwood-Randall will meet with leaders from the region to discuss opportunities for economic development, stability, and strengthening American partnerships. U.S. Special Representative for Afghanistan Reconciliation Ambassador Zalmay Khalilzad will also join the delegation for diplomatic engagements with President Ashraf Ghani of Afghanistan and leaders from other regional countries. The discussions will focus on promoting peace, security, and development in Afghanistan, as well as advancing shared regional security interests, including counterterrorism cooperation.